
reZet80 SCOUT 2-digit display specs [last modified: 2021-11-23]
---------------------------------------------------------------

The reZet80 SCOUT uses a 2-digit 7-segment LED display.
It displays 2 hexadecimal numbers.
The display has been designed for common cathode LED displays.
It uses the output I/O port (see specs_RXM_IO).

Please note that the decimal point (DP) is wired in hardware but not enabled
in software in the current version.

Bill of materials:
- 2x 1-digit common cathode LED display
- 2x resistor 1k
- 2x NPN transistor 160 mA
